{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_5ejoslm4qk41q9c56e2587","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"228520632","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-21T17-57-52-415Z/context-mode-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nA simple cache implementation using a `Map` as the underlying data store.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance.\n\n```javascript\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\nReturns an object with the following cache operations.\n\n## Methods\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves the cached value for the given key.\n\n```javascript\ncache.get('my-key')\n```\n\nReturns the value associated with the key, or `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nSets a value in the cache for the given key.\n\n```javascript\ncache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n```\n\nReturns the value that was set.\n\n### delete(key)\n\nRemoves a value from the cache for the given key.\n\n```javascript\ncache.delete('my-key')\n```\n\nReturns `true` if the key was deleted, `false` otherwise.\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all values from the cache.\n\n```javascript\ncache.clear()\n```\n\nReturns `void`.\n"}}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":12362,"output_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":12032},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4854277e-1961-4a7d-b4ce-ba88e08bb19d","uuid":"57208057-2fb8-4ae1-bc9e-0990d63bde31","timestamp":"2026-07-21T23:32:32.993Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"228520632","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-21T17-57-52-415Z/context-mode-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4854277e-1961-4a7d-b4ce-ba88e08bb19d","uuid":"fbbe6d40-2a70-4f0a-8073-50bb17a14eaf","timestamp":"2026-07-21T23:32:33.082Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-21T17-57-52-415Z/context-mode-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nA simple cache implementation using a `Map` as the underlying data store.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance.\n\n```javascript\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\nReturns an object with the following cache operations.\n\n## Methods\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves the cached value for the given key.\n\n```javascript\ncache.get('my-key')\n```\n\nReturns the value associated with the key, or `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nSets a value in the cache for the given key.\n\n```javascript\ncache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n```\n\nReturns the value that was set.\n\n### delete(key)\n\nRemoves a value from the cache for the given key.\n\n```javascript\ncache.delete('my-key')\n```\n\nReturns `true` if the key was deleted, `false` otherwise.\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all values from the cache.\n\n```javascript\ncache.clear()\n```\n\nReturns `void`.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
